## 7 Discussion

In this work, we propose BayesDAG, a novel, scalable Bayesian causal discovery framework that employs SG-MCMC (and VI) to infer causal models. We establish the validity of performing Bayesian inference in the augmented \((\bm{W},\bm{p})\) space and demonstrate its connection to permutation-based DAG learning. Furthermore, we provide two instantiations of the proposed framework that offers direct DAG sampling and model-agnosticism to linear and nonlinear relations. We demonstrate superior inference accuracy and scalability on various datasets. Future work can address some limitations: (1) designing better variational networks \(\mu_{\phi}\) to capture the complex distributions of \(\bm{W}\) compared to the simple independent Bernoulli distribution; (2) improving the performance of SG-MCMC with continuous relaxation (Appendix A), which currently does not align with its theoretical advantages compared to the SG-MCMC+VI counterpart.

